---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro'
import { detectorSpecs } from '@decoding/spec-registry'
---

<Layout
  title="Methodology — decod.ing"
  description="How decod.ing detects formats, handles ambiguity, and enforces local safety limits."
>
  <article class="prose container">
    <span class="eyebrow">Auditable method</span><h1>Confidence is evidence, not a guess.</h1>
    <p class="lead">
      Eight detector families score syntax, magic bytes, structure, and decoded output. A result
      auto-expands only above 85% confidence with at least a 15-point lead.
    </p>
    <h2>Supported detector families</h2><ul>
      {
        detectorSpecs.map((spec) => (
          <li>
            <a href={`/detect/${spec.slug}/`}>{spec.label}</a> — {spec.description}
          </li>
        ))
      }
    </ul>
    <h2>Recursive chain</h2><p>
      A selected candidate can produce another local input. The engine follows up to 8 levels and 64
      nodes while detecting cycles.
    </p>
    <h2>Safety limits</h2><p>
      Input is capped at 10 MiB, expanded output at 32 MiB, compression at 100:1, and a local
      operation at 2 seconds. Limits produce an explicit partial result rather than freezing the
      page.
    </p>
    <h2>What decod.ing does not claim</h2><p>
      Decoded JWT signatures are not verified without a trusted key. X.509 trust and revocation are
      not validated. A high-confidence format match does not make the content trustworthy.
    </p>
  </article>
</Layout>
